<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06061205 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06061205 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Pleasanton police are warning people that a male caller identifying himself asa PGandamp;E representative, who orders residents to evacuate their homes because ofa gas leak, is not from the power company. Police say the man has called atleast six people in the past month. In the event of a true evacuation, PacificGas andamp; Electric Co. employees would go door to door in uniform advisingresidents of the situation. Anyone receiving this type of call should callPleasanton police at (415) 484-8127.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  EVACUATION CALLS ARE BOGUS IN PLEASANTON  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Peninsula/AM  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910301  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  March  </MONTH><PG.COL>  11B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  90  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday March 1, 199100061205,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>